description:
Athina is an end-to-end platform for product teams building production-grade AI features.

1. Prototype: Dynamic Columns let you run LLM prompts, execute code, make API calls, retrieve data, run transformations, and more (in a spreadsheet UI)

2. Evaluate: Run evaluations within the sheet itself - there are 50+ preset evaluation metrics or you can create your own custom evals (no-code).

3. Experiment: Change your prompt, model, retriever, or chain in just a few clicks. Technical users can run even more experiments programmatically.

We’re on a mission to enable everyone to build reliable AI agents & AI applications. We're fully open source, and provide a unique integrated development & observability experience for those building anything in the AI space. This is the first step towards laying the foundations for Composable AI Systems; all AI systems need observability and introspection to be first class for them to be reliable.

How? We're standardizing how people write python to express data, ML, LLM, & agent workflows/pipelines/applications with lightweight frameworks. So that no matter the author, it'll be easy to collaborate, connect, and importantly in one line integrate observability and datastore needs. This speeds up time to production and reduces TCO because code remains easy to maintain and your data flywheel stays manageable. So you can increase the top line & bottom line of your business by delivering on AI that is reliable.

We've got two open source projects:
- one focused on AI applications, called Burr (https://github.com/dagworks-inc/burr).
- one focused on AI pipelines/workflows, called Hamilton (https://github.com/dagworks-inc/hamilton) see https://www.tryhamilton.dev

### Forfeit: Locking Down Habits with a Penalty

#### Overview
Founded in 2022 and hailing from the Y Combinator Batch W23, Forfeit is a unique productivity app situated in New York that's on a mission to help users cement their habits—under the threat of losing their own money. The central idea is straightforward, yet powerful: declare what you plan to do, set a deadline, and attach a financial penalty if you don’t deliver. If you fail to submit proof of your completion—be it a photo or a timelapse—your stake is gone.

### How It Works
1. **Set Your Intentions**: You articulate a specific habit or task, along with a time frame for completion and the amount of money you'll lose if you don't follow through.
2. **Provide Evidence**: By your deadline, send proof via a photo or capture a timelapse of you completing the task.
3. **Verification**: Your submission is either verified by AI or a human, ensuring accountability.
4. **Consequences**: Miss the deadline or provide invalid proof? Sorry, you lose the stake.

#### Why It Matters
In a world rife with distractions, Forfeit taps into the psychology of accountability. It’s the digital version of putting your money where your mouth is. With features that allow syncing with platforms like Apple Health or using timelapses, it's designed for everyone—from fitness buffs wanting to hit the gym regularly to students trying to meet their study goals.

### Statistics That Speak
- **Forfeits Set**: 371k
- **Total USD Staked**: $4.7M
- **Success Rate**: An impressive 94.2%

#### Target Audience
Forfeit appeals to those serious about enhancing their productivity—particularly individuals battling procrastination, and even those with mental health challenges (like ADHD) that make sticking to habits troublesome. It’s like having a financial coach at your fingertips.

### User Experiences
Testimonials paint a rosy picture. Users report life-altering outcomes—better mental health, improved fitness, and a newfound sense of discipline. Whether it’s Zane from the USA, who feels his life’s trajectory would’ve changed if this app had been around longer, or Brice in Austria, who credits Forfeit for his turn from a habit-breaking lifestyle to achieving tangible goals, the stories resonate.

### The Team
With a minimalist setup of just two employees, Forfeit remains agile. They're backed by Dalton Caldwell as a group partner, showcasing the commitment to maintaining high operational standards.

### The Future
Imagine a feature where failed forfeits could automatically contribute to a charity or a friend. That’s the think tank behind Forfeit—constantly evolving to provide more value to users.

### In Summary
Forfeit isn’t just an app; it's a commitment device that flips the script on willpower. If achieving your goals often feels like a tug-of-war with your own motivation, Forfeit could be the ally you need—just beware, those stakes can truly hurt. If you're ready to test your resolve, why not give it a shot?

Helicone.ai is creating an advanced observability platform tailored for developers working with Large Language Models (LLMs). Our goal is to simplify and enhance the operational side of deploying these models, making it easier for developers to monitor, manage, and optimize their AI applications at scale. Helicone provides a unified view of performance, cost, and user interaction metrics for various LLM providers, like OpenAI, Anthropic, and LangChain, empowering developers to make their LLM deployments more efficient, reliable, and cost-effective.

### Key Features

1. **Centralized Observability**: Our platform captures and visualizes detailed logs and metrics across all LLM deployments. With tools for prompt management, performance tracing, and debugging, Helicone provides real-time insights into the inner workings of your LLMs.

2. **LLM Performance Optimization**: Helicone supports prompt experimentation, success rate tracking, and fine-tuning, allowing you to continuously improve response quality and efficiency. This level of insight makes it easier to deliver high-performing, cost-effective AI applications.

3. **Flexible Data Management**: We understand that data privacy is critical. Helicone supports deployment options for dedicated instances, hybrid cloud integrations, or self-hosted environments, allowing clients to maintain control over their data and ensuring compliance with privacy standards.

### Built for Developers and Data Scientists

Helicone is designed to meet the needs of engineers and data scientists who require transparency and control over their LLMs. From chatbots to document processing systems, Helicone equips you with the insights needed to track costs, understand user interactions, and optimize outputs—all from one intuitive platform.

By combining observability with LLM-specific insights, Helicone is redefining AI monitoring, empowering developers to deploy and scale their AI models with confidence.

**Mission**
The core mission of Reflex is straightforward: simplify web application development. It champions an ecosystem of open-source tools and hosted services that empower developers to create applications faster, while maintaining robust customizability, flexibility, and performance. 

**Key Features**
- **Unified Development**: Build both frontend and backend using pure Python, making the development process seamless.
- **Quick Deployment**: With just one command (`reflex deploy`), you can deploy your application effortlessly.
- **High-Level UI Components**: Reflex offers over 60 built-in components for crafting user interfaces without needing to dive into JavaScript.
- **Integration with AI**: Developers can utilize AI agents to bolster their applications without added complexity.
- **Responsive Design**: Applications built with Reflex are designed to look great on any device, with options for dark and light modes.

Reflex has garnered a welcoming community, supported by a growing Discord presence and over 21,500 GitHub stars. Developers can freely contribute to the project or self-host the framework, as it's released under the Apache 2.0 license.

- It is already trusted by industry giants like Amazon, NASA, and IBM, showcasing its robust utility and trustworthiness.

**Getting Started**
To join the ranks of developers leveraging Reflex, you simply need to install it via pip (`pip install reflex`) and get started on your projects. You can check out the documentation [here](https://reflex.dev/docs/getting-started/introduction/) for a comprehensive guide.

Reflex isn't just another framework; it's a paradigm shift towards simplifying web application development in Python. If you're a Python developer aiming to build web applications efficiently, Reflex is worth a look.

description:
Sage is a self-generating, self-maintaining knowledge base for your code with in-built chat, accelerating expertise, and comprehension of any codebase.

Documentation is perpetually stale, codebases become increasingly old, large, and complex, and knowledge remains siloed within individuals and teams. As a result, engineers take 8-12 months to become fully operational, enterprise code becomes slow and unmaintainable, and core knowledge is continually lost upon engineer turnover.

Sage is changing this reality. We take your code and automatically generate a symbol-level knowledge base that self-updates to remain forever fresh. We integrate with source control to pull your code and generate a symbolic graph representation of functions, classes, interfaces, types, etc., automatically determining the relevant context for each symbol, and using LLMs to annotate and propagate documentation via traversals of the symbol graph. 

Sage revolutionizes the way teams and individuals interact with and understand their code, ensuring that knowledge is always accessible, up-to-date, and interactive.

**Sage AI: Empowering Code Knowledge**

Founded in 2023 as part of the Y Combinator Batch W23, Sage AI is shaking up the software development landscape. Based in San Francisco and operated by a compact yet capable team of two, Sage AI is on a mission to transform the way developers interact with their codebases. Its core proposition is straightforward yet powerful: a self-generating, self-maintaining code knowledge base.

### The Problem
In the modern software environment, documentation often lags, codebases grow unwieldy, and critical knowledge tends to be trapped within individual team members. This situation results in engineers spending anywhere from 8 to 12 months to reach full operational efficiency. As code becomes sluggish and unmanageable, the loss of core knowledge due to team turnover exacerbates these issues.

### The Solution
Enter Sage AI. By automatically generating a symbol-level knowledge base from your code, Sage ensures that crucial information is always fresh and readily accessible. The company integrates seamlessly with your source control, pulling in your code to create a symbolic graph representation of its various components—functions, classes, and other interfaces. Leveraging large language models (LLMs), Sage annotates and propagates documentation throughout this graph, continually updating the knowledge base with the context necessary for understanding.

### The Impact
Sage AI is set to revolutionize how both teams and individuals comprehend their code. With its innovative approach, the platform guarantees that knowledge remains not only accessible but interactive and continuously relevant—a game-changer in a world where information silos can hinder progress and innovation.

In a nutshell, Sage AI is here to help developers overcome common pitfalls associated with legacy code management and knowledge retention, fostering an environment where expertise can thrive. 

You can check them out at [sage-ai.dev](https://sage-ai.dev) and watch how they redefine developer tools with AI. 

In a space marked by complexity, Sage AI promises to simplify, enhance, and sustain your coding expertise.

Sanvivo builds a multisided platform to enable customers to order medications, get pharmaceutical advice, and book health services at local pharmacies in Europe. Just like Shopify for pharmacies.

Sanvivo gives pharmacies software to take, fill and schedule delivery for online orders. We also bring instant demand through integrations with 3rd party consumer delivery companies.

**Company Overview**  
Founded in 2022 and situated in Tel Aviv-Yafo, Israel, Sherloq is an innovative startup that's a part of Y Combinator's Batch W23. With a small, agile team of six, Sherloq tackles a big issue faced by data-driven organizations: the inconsistency and fragmentation in SQL code management among data analysts.

**Mission**  
Sherloq’s mission is straightforward yet powerful: to provide a single source of truth for all SQL queries directly within users' SQL editors. This eliminates the chaotic reliance on various tools such as notepads, Slack channels, or Word documents.

**The Problem They Solve**  
In many companies, two data analysts tasked with the same question often end up with wildly different results—a symptom of the way SQL is typically managed. Sherloq addresses this by simplifying and centralizing SQL management, allowing teams to share, edit, and document queries seamlessly.

**How It Works**  
Sherloq functions as a plugin that integrates directly into existing query editors, bridging the gap between analysts and their queries without requiring them to change their workflow. Features include query saving, sharing capabilities, version control, and an extensive history of previous queries—making SQL interactions smoother and more efficient.

**Tooling and Resources**  
The company doesn't just stop at query management. They offer various FREE tools for data professionals, such as:
- **AI SQL Syntax Validator**: Ensures correctness in SQL queries.
- **AI SQL Organizer**: Helps organize and manage SQL snippets.
- **SQL Visual Tool (ERD)**: Provides visual representations of databases.
- **SQL Formatting**: Enhances query readability.
- **SQL Greeting Generator**: Adds a personalized touch to queries.

And there’s a Chrome extension and an IntelliJ plugin to get users up and running in no time.

**Why Choose Sherloq?**  
Current solutions like GitHub or Confluence can be overkill for SQL management, while simpler options like Notepad don't cut it either. Sherloq's user-centric design helps professionals streamline their day-to-day operations, saving time and reducing errors. Plus, it keeps security and compliance top-of-mind, being SOC2 compliant and ensuring data integrity.

**Customer Feedback**  
Users have been raving about Sherloq’s practicality. Not only does it simplify the saving and sharing of queries, but it also reduces the time spent searching for important SQL code scattered across multiple platforms. Testimonials highlight the satisfaction of having a structured tool that logs queries and provides easy categorization and sharing.

**Looking Ahead**  
As a product designed by data users for data users, Sherloq shapes its development around the evolving needs of teams. The tool's rapid onboarding and intuitive design make it an attractive choice for organizations that prioritize effective data analysis while striving to maintain consistency.

In summary, Sherloq is more than just a plugin—it's a revolution in how companies manage, document, and collaborate on SQL queries, ultimately bringing clarity to something that often feels chaotic. Keep an eye on Sherloq as it continues to innovate and refine the landscape of SQL management.

description:
## What is Yuma AI?

Yuma is automating customer support by providing an AI Support Agent orchestration platform. Yuma provides autonomous AI agents dedicated to customer service and e-commerce.

We integrate directly with help desk software (Zendesk, Kustomer, Gorgias, etc.) and focus on helping large Shopify merchants deal with their high volume of support requests.

Top merchants using Yuma can automate up to 60% of their support tickets fully autonomously.

## Why do Shopify merchants need Yuma?

There are thousands of large Shopify merchants around the world generating $10M+ a year. Most of them have taken over some niches and are great at what they do: selling their products.

But they all have one thing in common: they all hate customer support. It's a burden for them and a huge source of cost, as they receive hundreds of requests per day. Some of them have dozens of support agents on staff, usually offshore, and the overall quality is still often pretty poor while staff turnover remains high.

Those merchants have been promised automation for years but have always been disappointed by the outcome. As customers, we have all had to live through a terrible support automation experience before, so this is no secret, and everyone knows that the current state of the technology is quite bad.

## Yuma is solving this in a few ways:

Yuma isn't just another RAG chatbot. Our platform provides autonomous AI agents dedicated to support and ecommerce.

These agents are powered by knowledge, follow processes, and are managed by our in-house AI orchestration technology. This ensures safety, control, and quality at every step.

We believe that to truly automate customer support, we must develop a platform that mimics the actions of a human support agent. That's exactly what we've been doing.

Currently, our top merchants are automating 60% of their support tickets through Yuma. Yuma can fetch information from external services and take actions in other apps as needed to resolve each ticket.

We are laser-focused on building the best AI support agent platform and aim to achieve 80% true automation in the next few months.

## Fun Fact

Yuma got started by accident. This is my third YC startup after Socialcam (W12) and Triplebyte (S15). I released Yuma as a prototype for fun in mid-December 2022 and was overwhelmed with demo requests. That's when I knew I was onto something and had to turn this into a real company, once again.

**Y Combinator:** Part of Batch W23  
**Group Partner:** Jared Friedman  

**Mission:** Yuma AI aims to be the ultimate AI support agent for e-commerce, revolutionizing customer service through automation.

---

### What is Yuma AI?

At its core, Yuma AI is about automating customer support specifically for e-commerce platforms. It offers an orchestration platform that deploys autonomous AI agents focused on enhancing customer service experiences for e-commerce businesses, primarily large Shopify merchants. By integrating seamlessly with help desk software such as Zendesk, Kustomer, and Gorgias, Yuma can handle a significant volume of daily support queries—up to 60% can be managed autonomously, drastically cutting down response times and operational costs.

---

### Challenges for Shopify Merchants

Many Shopify merchants, particularly those generating over $10 million annually, excel at selling but dread customer support—a task that often leads to high costs and frustrating experiences. With countless support requests flooding in daily, many merchants are stuck with high agent turnover and unsatisfactory service quality. They’ve been promised automated solutions in the past, which often fell short of expectations, resulting in poor customer interactions.

---

### How Yuma AI is Different

Yuma sets itself apart by not being just another generic AI chatbot. It leverages proprietary orchestration technology to train its agents in real e-commerce scenarios. These agents possess specialized knowledge and understand the processes necessary for effective support—this isn’t just a superficial interaction. Instead, Yuma's agents act like human agents, retrieving information from various external services and taking actionable steps to resolve customer issues.

Yuma AI aims to push true automation further, targeting an impressive 80% automation rate in the near future.

---

### Exciting Beginnings

Interestingly, Yuma AI's journey started as an unplanned side project—a prototype released in December 2022 was met with overwhelming interest, prompting the founders to embrace the opportunity and develop it into a fully-fledged startup.

---

### Core Features

- **Autonomous Ticket Handling:** Automates 60% of customer support tickets, allowing human agents to focus on more complex inquiries.
- **Integration with Major Platforms:** Works with widely used e-commerce and help desk systems to provide a streamlined support experience.
- **Pre-trained Knowledge Base:** Equipped with a rich repository of e-commerce data to answer customer inquiries accurately and promptly.
- **Scalability:** Supports scaling operations seamlessly without needing proportional increases in human resources.

---

### Why It Matters

In today's competitive online retail landscape, customer experience is paramount. Yuma AI not only empowers brands to manage customer support efficiently but also helps them maintain high satisfaction levels while reducing costs—this is the sweet spot many businesses aim for.

---

### In Summary

Yuma AI is a promising player in the customer support realm for e-commerce, cleverly leveraging AI to tackle a painfully common problem. With its laser focus on automation and integration, Yuma is well-positioned to transform how online retailers manage customer interactions, leading to happier customers and healthier businesses. If you're a Shopify merchant weary of managing support tickets, Yuma might just be the boost you need.
